The paper focuses on generating layouts for graphic design and scene generation, which involves computer vision (CV) and graphics (GR) techniques. The proposed method uses a Generative Adversarial Network (GAN), which is a popular technique in artificial intelligence (AI) research. The paper also mentions the use of self-attention modules, which are commonly used in deep learning (LG) research. Finally, the experiments involve generating various types of graphics, which could fall under multimedia (MM) research.
